formatted-text.run: Trends in Product Discontinuations Overtime by Subcategory Line Graph

Here, CDPHId is used as a unique product identifier to count distinct discontinued products over may years.This line graph illustrates the distinct count of products discontinued over time, separated by color by subcategories. Peaks in certain years highlight potential regulatory impacts, market shifts, or changes in consumer demand.

Chemical Count Reporting Overtime Line Graph

This line grapgh shows trends in initial reporting dates and chemical dislosure counts over time. For example, peaks in the fall season months may indicate increased product innovations, especially for the Makeup Products Category. The correlation between categories may represent changes in chemical reporting and events like product launches, regulatory deadlines, or industry focus shifts.
